(11,1,"2018-12-07 13:34:58","2018-12-07 13:34:58","<b>CARE</b> (<b>Cooperative for Assistance and Relief Everywhere</b>, formerly <b>Cooperative for American Remittances to Europe</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CARE_(relief_agency)#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>) is a major international <a title=\"Humanitarian aid\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Humanitarian_aid\">humanitarian agency</a> delivering emergency relief and long-term <a title=\"International development\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_development\">international development</a> projects. Founded in 1945, CARE is <a title=\"Nonsectarian\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonsectarian\">nonsectarian</a>, impartial, and <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Non-governmental\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental\">non-governmental</a>. It is one of the largest and oldest humanitarian aid organizations focused on fighting global poverty. In 2016, CARE reported working in 94 countries, supporting 962 <a title=\"Poverty\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poverty\">poverty</a>-fighting projects and humanitarian aid projects, and reaching over 80 million people and 256 million people indirectly.","Refreshed","","publish","closed","closed","","refreshed","","","2018-12-07 13:34:58","2018-12-07 13:34:58","",0,"http://tabasum-group-of-companies.local/?page_id=11",0,"page","",0),
