(13,1,"2018-12-07 13:35:41","2018-12-07 13:35:41","he first CARE Packages were in fact surplus <a title=\"10-in-1 food parcel\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/10-in-1_food_parcel\">“Ten-in-One” US army rations packs</a> (designed to contain a day\'s meals for ten people).<sup id=\"cite_ref-O’Keefe_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CARE_(relief_agency)#cite_note-O%E2%80%99Keefe-4\">[4]</a></sup> In early 1946 CARE purchased 2.8 million of these warehoused rations packs, originally intended for the <a title=\"Operation Downfall\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Downfall\">invasion of Japan</a>, and began advertising in America. On May 11, 1946, six months after the agency\'s incorporation, the first CARE Packages were delivered in <a title=\"Le Havre\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Le_Havre\">Le Havre</a>, <a title=\"France\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France\">France</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Morris_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CARE_(relief_agency)#cite_note-Morris-6\">[6]</a></sup> These packages contained staples such as <a title=\"Canning\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canning\">canned</a>meats, <a title=\"Powdered milk\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Powdered_milk\">powdered milk</a>, <a title=\"Dried fruit\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dried_fruit\">dried fruits</a>, and <a title=\"Fat\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fat\">fats</a> along with a few comfort items such as <a title=\"Chocolate\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chocolate\">chocolate</a>, <a title=\"Coffee\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coffee\">coffee</a>, and <a title=\"Cigarette\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cigarette\">cigarettes</a>. (Several on the CARE <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Board of Directors\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Board_of_Directors\">Board of Directors</a>wished to remove the cigarettes, but it was deemed impractical to open and reseal 2.8 million boxes.)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Morris_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CARE_(relief_agency)#cite_note-Morris-6\">[6]</a></sup> 1946 also marked CARE\'s first expansion out of the US with the establishment of an office in <a title=\"Canada\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada\">Canada</a>","NewButton","","publish","closed","closed","","newbutton","","","2018-12-07 13:35:41","2018-12-07 13:35:41","",0,"http://tabasum-group-of-companies.local/?page_id=13",0,"page","",0),
